Patron Frequency Plot

2022-11-03

There are 214418 unique words in the data set across all three time periods.

There are 813 unique words that occur more than 1000 times across all three time periods.

575 of these are four characters or longer.

Well now take the top 1000, 100, and 50 most frequently used terms from each time frame. Well then plot the frequency of these words if, and only if, they occur in all three time periods.

Working with the 1000 most frequently used terms, there are 1135 unique terms in total, of which 871 are in all three time periods, and 264 are in only 1 or 2 of the time separated data sets.

If we plot the 871 words that occur more than 1000 times in all three data sets, this is what we get:

  • Blue = pre-pandemic
  • Red = main-pandemic
  • green = late pandemic

We can see that red is always higher than green which is always higher than blue.

Working with the 100 most frequently used terms, there are 109 unique terms in total, of which 92 are in all three time periods, and 17 are in only 1 or 2 of the time separated data sets.

Working with the 50 most frequently used terms, there are 56 unique terms in total, of which 45 are in all three time periods, and 11 are in only 1 or 2 of the time separated data sets.
